I've updated the plan based on your feedback. The key changes:

1. Resolved the scripted-behavior-across-subprocess-boundary CRITICAL: one built-in profile baked into each worker host. The existing ScriptedX callable-injected classes stay for in-process tests; only the new service wrappers use the fixed profile. Knobs exposed as CLI flags (--proposals-per-plan, --fail-every). A --profile flag is deliberately NOT introduced.

2. Resolved the implementer-repo CRITICAL: implementer host gets --repo-path, writes real orphan commits on work/* branches using GitRepo, and the planner emits proposals with parent_commits=() so the Integrator's reachability check passes trivially. Orchestrator and implementer share the bare-repo path. No --base-ref needed.

3. Resolved the ID-allocation suggestion: worker-generated IDs are <role>-<uuid>, prefix-based flags dropped for proposals/trials. Orchestrator-allocated task IDs keep readable prefixes but append a short UUID.

4. Rewrote the auth addendum without the 'MAY, but MUST NOT' contradiction — now reads as a plain MAY with the one real constraint (no overloading of the normative eden://error/... vocabulary for auth outcomes).

