   692	
   693	## Known risks
   694	
   695	- **Subprocess-based integration tests are easy to write wrong.** The
   696	  E2E spec above is explicit about: ephemeral ports announced on
   697	  stdout; stderr capture on failure; bounded timeouts at every wait
   698	  point; SIGKILL fallback on SIGTERM timeout; tempdir teardown on
   699	  every exit path. Missing any of these yields a test that hangs CI
   700	  or produces unrunnable "red for unknown reason" failures. These
   701	  are codified in the test, not left to diligence.
   702	- **Auth in the non-normative namespace is a cross-concern edit.**
   703	  `eden_wire.errors._TYPE_BY_EXC` currently maps only `StorageError`
   704	  subclasses to `eden://error/…`. The new `Unauthorized` exception
   705	  lives outside that map because (a) it's not a `StorageError`, and
   706	  (b) it's reference-only. Keep the two tables clearly separated so
   707	  no future refactor accidentally leaks a reference-only type into
   708	  the normative vocabulary.
   709	- **Workers don't self-terminate.** Anything that boots a worker
   710	  (test harness, future deployment) is responsible for killing it.
   711	  SIGTERM triggers a clean exit within one poll interval; SIGKILL
   712	  is the fallback after 10 seconds. Documented in each service's
   713	  README.
   714	- **Shared-token auth has no transport security.** The server is
   715	  loopback-only in tests and documented as such. A real deployment
   716	  of shared-token auth over a non-TLS link leaks the token. Auth
   717	  scaffolding has a big caveat in its README pointing at Milestone
   718	  3.
   719	- **Windows signal handling.** `signal.SIGTERM` on Windows is
   720	  missing; uvicorn's shutdown path uses `SIGBREAK` / SIGINT. The
   721	  E2E test is `pytest.mark.skipif(sys.platform == "win32", …)`.
   722	  Non-test code paths also work on Windows (uvicorn handles it),
   723	  just not exercised in CI.
   724	- **Quiescence counter ≥ 2.** If
   725	  `--max-quiescent-iterations` is 1, the orchestrator can exit
   726	  while a worker is mid-submit (the orchestrator reads tasks, sees
   727	  nothing pending, exits; the worker's submit lands a moment
   728	  later, orphaned). Default of 3 plus a poll interval of 0.1s
   729	  means we wait ~0.2s of no-progress, which empirically covers
   730	  scripted-worker latency with a wide margin. Documented as a
   731	  tunable.
   732	- **Ephemeral port assignment race.** We bind `--port 0`, read the
   733	  port from stdout, then launch other processes pointing at it.
   734	  Between `listen()` and the port being printed there's a
   735	  flush-timing window where the harness might read an empty line;
   736	  the harness must `readline()` in a loop until it gets the
   737	  `EDEN_TASK_STORE_LISTENING` prefix. Harness code handles this.
   738	- **`--plan-tasks N` (integer) vs explicit list.** The integer form
   739	  is the common case; the explicit-list form exists so tests can
   740	  pin deterministic IDs that assertions can reference.
   741	- **Scripted `plan_fn` / `implement_fn` / `evaluate_fn` now live in
   742	  shared code.** Tests that used to inject their own fn still can,
   743	  by importing and parameterizing — no lock-in. The shared
   744	  defaults are the deterministic "3 trials, all succeed" shape
   745	  that the Phase 5 / 7b E2E uses.
   746	
   747	## Execution order
   748	
   749	This is execution-only; no scope decisions are deferred to here.
   750	
