   150	
   151	### 5.1 Fields
   152	
   153	| Field | Required | Type | Description |
   154	|---|---|---|---|
   155	| `proposal_id` | yes | string | Unique identifier. |
   156	| `experiment_id` | yes | string | The experiment this proposal belongs to. |
   157	| `slug` | yes | string | Human-readable short label. MUST match `^[a-z0-9][a-z0-9-]*$`. |
   158	| `priority` | yes | number | Ordering hint; higher dispatches earlier. |
   159	| `parent_commits` | yes | array of SHA | One or more commit SHAs the proposal is based on. |
   160	| `artifacts_uri` | yes | string (URI) | Where the planner's output documents live. |
   161	| `state` | yes | string | One of `"drafting"`, `"ready"`, `"dispatched"`, `"completed"`. `"completed"` is terminal and means the implementer's attempt has finished (successfully or not); the trial's `status` records the outcome (see [`04-task-protocol.md`](04-task-protocol.md) §7). |
   162	| `created_at` | yes | timestamp | When the proposal was created. |
   163	
   164	### 5.2 Parent commits
   165	
   166	`parent_commits` MUST contain at least one SHA. Each SHA MUST name a commit reachable from the experiment's starting commit on `main` or from an already-completed trial on the canonical trial lineage.
   167	
   168	## 6. Metrics schema
   169	
   170	Schema: [`schemas/metrics-schema.schema.json`](schemas/metrics-schema.schema.json).
   171	
   172	A metrics schema is a mapping from metric name to storage type. It appears as the `metrics_schema` field of an experiment config and is used to validate every metrics payload the evaluator produces.
   173	
   174	### 6.1 Shape
   175	
   176	The metrics schema is a JSON object whose keys are metric names and whose values are type strings.
   177	
   178	- A metric name MUST match `^[A-Za-z_][A-Za-z0-9_]*$`.
   179	- A type value MUST be one of `"integer"`, `"real"`, `"text"`.
   180	- A metrics schema MUST have at least one entry.
   181	
   182	### 6.2 Reserved names
   183	
   184	The names `trial_id`, `commit_sha`, `parent_commits`, `branch`, `status`, `artifacts_uri`, `description`, `timestamp`, `started_at`, `completed_at` are reserved by the protocol for use on the trial object and MUST NOT appear in a metrics schema.
   185	
   186	## 7. Trial
   187	
   188	Schema: [`schemas/trial.schema.json`](schemas/trial.schema.json).
   189	
   190	A trial is one completed attempt.
   191	
   192	### 7.1 Fields
   193	
   194	| Field | Required | Type | Description |
   195	|---|---|---|---|
   196	| `trial_id` | yes | string | Unique identifier. |
   197	| `experiment_id` | yes | string | The experiment this trial belongs to. |
   198	| `proposal_id` | yes | string | The proposal that produced this trial. |
   199	| `status` | yes | string | One of `"starting"`, `"success"`, `"error"`, `"eval_error"`. |
   200	| `parent_commits` | yes | array of SHA | Inherited from the proposal. |
   201	| `branch` | no | string | Worker branch under `work/*`. Present once the implementer starts. |
   202	| `commit_sha` | no | string | Worker-branch tip SHA. Present once the implementer completes. |
   203	| `trial_commit_sha` | no | string | Canonical-lineage SHA under `trial/*`. Present once the integrator has promoted the trial. |
   204	| `artifacts_uri` | no | string (URI) | Where the trial's artifacts live. |
   205	| `description` | no | string | Human-readable summary. |
   206	| `metrics` | no | object | Metrics payload; shape dictated by the experiment's metrics schema. |
   207	| `started_at` | yes | timestamp | When the implementer began. |
   208	| `completed_at` | no | timestamp | Set when the trial reaches a terminal status. Written exactly once by the orchestrator, atomically with the transition from `"starting"` to `"success"`, `"error"`, or `"eval_error"` (see [`04-task-protocol.md`](04-task-protocol.md) §4.3 and [`03-roles.md`](03-roles.md) §4.4). |
